        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-27T04:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-27T04:35:00-05:00" n="431" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.91/11–2745: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-27T13:00:00+03:25">November 27, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 27—12:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1007. Embtel 990, November 24. Soviet Embassy yesterday issued passes to Embassy
                    personnel to proceed to Tabriz. Capt Gagarine departed yesterday afternoon by
                    car and Major Garver and Jernegan this morning by air.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept as 1007, repeated Moscow as 295.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
